### Test 1: Register with invalid email (should fail)
POST http://localhost:54955/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "invalid-email",
    "password": "pass123",
    "firstName": "John"
}

### Expected Response:
{
    "status": 400,
    "message": "Validation failed",
    "errors": {
        "email": "Please provide a valid email address"
    }
}

### Test 2: Register with weak password (should fail)
POST http://localhost:54955/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "test@example.com",
    "password": "weak",
    "firstName": "John",
    "lastName": "Doe"
}

### Expected Response: Password must be at least 6 characters

### Test 3: Register with valid data (should succeed)
POST http://localhost:54955/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "valid@example.com",
    "password": "StrongP@ss123",
    "firstName": "John",
    "lastName": "Doe"
}

### Test 4: Create product with invalid price (should fail)
POST http://localhost:54955/api/products
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer ADMIN_TOKEN

{
    "name": "Test",
    "sku": "TEST001",
    "price": -10.99,
    "stockQuantity": 10
}

### Expected Response: Price must be greater than 0

### Test 5: Create order with invalid payment method (should fail)
POST http://localhost:54955/api/orders
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer USER_TOKEN

{
    "shippingAddress": "123 Main St",
    "billingAddress": "123 Main St",
    "paymentMethod": "INVALID_METHOD"
}
